title: runtime: signal_windows_386.c:73 set and not used: gp
body:
What steps will reproduce the problem?
1. compile Go on windows x32
or 
1. recompile package (with `go get -a -u`)

What is the expected output?
All test passed/ no output for go get

What do you see instead?
Warnings:
# runtime
warning: C:\Go\src\pkg\runtime\signal_windows_386.c:73 set and not used: gp

Which compiler are you using (5g, 6g, 8g, gccgo)?
8g

Which operating system are you using?
Windows 7 x32

Which version are you using?  (run 'go version')
go version devel +036190b86798 Sat Feb 02 12:39:04 2013 +0100 windows/386

Please provide any additional information below.
Everything seems working fine.
